txt.en: 'I heard you are going a-hunting. While you are out there, do me a favour and check some of my traps? They can be found by the river and among the trees.'
Elgur is in Amdân.\n\nYou should bring the fish and critters to Elgur.
'Excellent work! The fish and critters will become food, supplies, and clothing for the army. It may not seem like a lot, but every little bit counts.'

Fish traps can be found around the shores of the nearby river. Traps for critters are scattered throughout the forests outside the eastern gate of Amdân.\n\nYou should check the traps for fish and critters.
'Excellent work! The fish and critters will become food, supplies, and clothing for the army. It may not seem like a lot, but every little bit counts.'
The dwarves have set traps about the valley, but can spare few to check the cages.
